texts.html: Bam! You should now be in the TARDIS’ bigger-on-the-inside (smaller-on-the-outside) interior.

texts.html: I figured it’d just be a single, static shot, but no:  you can click all around the control room, complete with StreetView’s signature panoramas, navigating all the way down below the main platform for a glimpse at the heart of the TARDIS itself. You don’t seem to be able to click into any of the hallways —  that’s probably for the better, really, as we don’t want any of you getting lost.

@virtualluffy the doorway is actually a wormhole to the Doctor's private space at the beginning of time, so he's not ever truly physically traveling through time, he's simulating the travel in time by creating holographic realities and simply taking that step out the door. Then, when he goes to return, a wormhole is created that reconnects him with 'the beginning', retaining the information from the trip and recreating that timeline on the next iteration, creating infinite variety through his constant attempts to understand how it all works and recover from his theft of the 'TARDIS' by returning the TARDIS to the rightful owner. .

The companions are an added bonus. Not sure if he's aware they are AI or not. But they are.
